.TH "snd_hdac_power_down_pm" 9 "snd_hdac_power_down_pm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_power_down_pm \- power down the codec
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hdac_power_down_pm
.BI "(struct hdac_device *codec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the codec object
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Like \fBsnd_hdac_power_up_pm\fP, this function is used in a recursive
code path like init code which may be called by PM suspend/resume again.

Returns zero if successful, or a negative error code.
